          "path": "literature/2101.10878/arxiv_source/paper.tex",
          "start_line": 159,
          "end_line": 159,
          "context": "we used the Milky Way mass model I of Irrgang et al. (2013), which is a three-component Galactic potential ..."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-09",
      "depends_on": [
        "step-06",
        "step-08"
      ],
      "step_type": "orbit_integration",
      "summary": "Backward orbit integration from current position to Galactic plane using fourth-order Runge-Kutta-Fehlberg method with adaptive step size. Plane crossing defined by vertical offset from mid-plane drawn from Gaussian (sigma=0.1 kpc for inner disk, sigma=5 kpc for r>16 kpc). 1 million Monte Carlo runs for error propagation. Derived plane-crossing positions (x_p, y_p, z_p, r_p), velocities (v_x,p, v_y,p, v_z,p, v_Grf,p), ejection velocity v_ej (relative to rotating disk), and flight time tau_flight (Table A.2).",
      "inputs": [
        "Current Galactocentric phase-space coordinates",
        "Galactic potential model",
        "Disk height distribution"
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "Plane-crossing parameters (r_p, v_ej, tau_flight)",
        "Ejection velocities"
      ],
      "parameters": [],
      "source_refs": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "path": "literature/2101.10878/arxiv_source/paper.tex",
          "start_line": 159,
          "end_line": 160,
          "context": "backward integration of the Monte Carlo orbits ... equations of motions are numerically solved ..."
        }
      ]
    },
